# Test: WithAssetEventsBB
# Purpose: Validates Bed & Breakfast matching combined with capital returns and
#          accumulation dividends adjusting the Section 104 cost base
# Rules Tested: Bed & Breakfast, Capital Returns (CAPRETURN), Accumulation
#               dividends (ACCUMULATION), Section 104 Pooling
# Complexity: Complex
# Key Features: Multi-year, CAPRETURN reduces pool cost, ACCUMULATION raises pool
#               cost, B&B match against a post-sale buy, two corporate-action pairs
# Expected Outcome: 2019/20 gain £280.91 (B&B leg £72.35 + Section 104 leg £208.56)
#
# Verification Status: Verified
# Verified By: Reconciled against golden output 2026-06-21
# Verification Notes: Matches tests/json/WithAssetEventsBB.json and
#                     tests/plain/WithAssetEventsBB.txt. See detailed verification below.
#
# === DETAILED VERIFICATION ===
#
# CHRONOLOGICAL ORDER:
# 1. 2018-08-29: BUY 20 @ £184.65 + £12.50 fees
# 2. 2019-03-15: BUY 20 @ £181.56 + £2.00 fees
# 3. 2019-05-31: CAPRETURN 40 shares, £149.75 total (reduces pool cost)
# 4. 2019-05-31: ACCUMULATION 40 shares, £150.24 total (raises pool cost basis)
# 5. 2019-11-05: SELL 40 @ £194.22 - £12.50 fees
# 6. 2019-11-10: BUY 20 @ £190.19 + £2.00 fees (B&B - within 30 days after the sale)
# 7. 2019-11-30: CAPRETURN 20 shares, £95.12 total (reduces pool cost)
# 8. 2019-11-30: ACCUMULATION 20 shares, £110.93 total (raises pool cost basis)
#
# Note: ACCUMULATION is a reinvested distribution. It pays no cash and is not a
# disposal, but it DOES increase the Section 104 cost basis (see spec.md
# "Accumulation Dividends"), so both pairs must be tracked through the pool.
#
# === SECTION 104 POOL (pre-sale) ===
#
# Transaction 1: 2018-08-29 BUY 20 shares
#   Cost: 20 × £184.65 + £12.50 = £3,705.50
#   Pool: 20 shares, £3,705.50
#
# Transaction 2: 2019-03-15 BUY 20 shares
#   Cost: 20 × £181.56 + £2.00 = £3,633.20
#   Pool: 40 shares, £7,338.70  (avg £183.4675/share)
#
# Transaction 3: 2019-05-31 CAPRETURN 40 shares, £149.75 total
#   Pool cost -= £149.75: £7,338.70 - £149.75 = £7,188.95
#   Pool: 40 shares, £7,188.95
#
# Transaction 4: 2019-05-31 ACCUMULATION 40 shares, £150.24 total
#   Pool cost += £150.24: £7,188.95 + £150.24 = £7,339.19
#   Pool: 40 shares, £7,339.19  (avg £183.47975/share)
#
# === DISPOSAL: 2019-11-05 SELL 40 shares ===
#
# Gross proceeds: 40 × £194.22 = £7,768.80
# Net proceeds:   £7,768.80 - £12.50 fees = £7,756.30
# Each 20-share leg's net proceeds: 20 × £194.22 - (£12.50 × 20/40)
#                                 = £3,884.40 - £6.25 = £3,878.15
#
# Matching order (CG51560): Same Day -> Bed & Breakfast -> Section 104
#   Same Day:    none
#   B&B:         20 shares matched to the 2019-11-10 buy (5 days after the sale)
#   Section 104: remaining 20 shares from the pool
#
# B&B leg (20 shares):
#   Priced off the raw target buy; a B&B-consumed share is never held at a later
#   corporate action, so no cost offset applies.
#   Allowable cost = 20 × £190.19 + £2.00 = £3,805.80
#   Gain = £3,878.15 - £3,805.80 = £72.35
#
# Section 104 leg (20 shares):
#   Priced off the live pool average at the disposal instant.
#   Unit cost = £7,339.19 / 40 = £183.47975/share
#   Allowable cost = 20 × £183.47975 = £3,669.595  ->  £3,669.60
#   Gain = £3,878.15 - £3,669.595 = £208.555  ->  £208.56
#   Pool drained: 40 - 20 = 20 shares; £7,339.19 - £3,669.595 = £3,669.595
#
# === SECTION 104 POOL (post-sale) ===
#
# The B&B-matched 2019-11-10 buy is fully consumed by the match, so none of it
# enters the pool (residue 0). The held 20 shares are the pool remainder.
#
# Transaction 7: 2019-11-30 CAPRETURN 20 shares, £95.12 total
#   Pool cost -= £95.12: £3,669.595 - £95.12 = £3,574.475
#   Pool: 20 shares, £3,574.475
#
# Transaction 8: 2019-11-30 ACCUMULATION 20 shares, £110.93 total
#   Pool cost += £110.93: £3,574.475 + £110.93 = £3,685.405  ->  £3,685.41
#   Pool: 20 shares, £3,685.41  (avg £184.27/share)
#
# === FINAL RESULT (2019/20) ===
#   Disposals: 1
#   Gross proceeds: £7,768.80
#   Net proceeds: £7,756.30
#   Total allowable cost: £3,805.80 + £3,669.60 = £7,475.40
#   Total gain: £72.35 + £208.56 = £280.91
#   Total loss: £0
#   Annual exemption: £12,000.00  ->  Taxable gain: £0.00
#   Final holding: 20 shares, £3,685.41 (avg £184.27/share)
#   Rule: Bed & Breakfast + Section 104
#   Verification: matches golden output
# === END DETAILED VERIFICATION ===
